    <note>
        <div>
            <p>The Foreign Service Act of 1980 (Oct 17, 1980; P.L. 96-465; 94 Stat. 2080) made the
                Inspector General a Presidential appointee, subject to the advice and consent of
                the Senate, and changed the title to Inspector General of the Department of State
                and the Foreign Service.</p>
